- Never invent rules, field lengths, formats, limits, entities, integrations, error codes,
  messages, or non-functional requirements the document does not support.
- Label every item by source:
    * STATED      — explicitly in the document. Present as fact.
    * (inferred)  — a reasonable implication of stated content. Append "(inferred)".
- Domain experience may SUGGEST inferred items, but general practice must NEVER be presented
  as a stated requirement. Where the document is silent, write "Not specified".
- Make each rule ATOMIC and individually testable — one rule per line. Split compound rules.
- Assign stable IDs: business rules BR-1...; workflows WF-1...
