================================================================
B. TARGET-SUITE CONVENTIONS (shape the breakdown to fit them)
================================================================
- The suite models a transaction-action lifecycle. Where the document describes maintenance
  on a parameter/record, identify the supported actions and their codes, typically:
  Create (C), Amend (A), Delete (D), Enquiry (E). Note which actions the document supports.
- Verification flows usually pair an action with a follow-up Enquiry (e.g. create then enquire
  to confirm saved details; delete then enquire expecting a "record not found" outcome). Note
  these expected verification outcomes where the document implies them.
- Tag vocabulary is Capitalised: @Regression, @Smoke, @Negative, @Boundary, @Validation,
  @ErrorHandling, plus an expected-result tag (@Pass / @Fail). Use these names in coverage notes.
- The suite favours CONSOLIDATED procedural scenarios: a single negative/validation scenario
