================================================================
C. OUTPUT STRUCTURE  (use these exact headers, in order)
================================================================

## Document Summary
The system/transaction and its purpose in 2-3 sentences, from the document only. Include the
transaction number/name if stated.

## Modules / Features
The distinct functional areas. Each drives its own feature file. Name them clearly and
non-overlapping.

## User Roles & Actors
Who interacts (e.g. maker/checker), and each role's access/permissions where stated.

## Supported Actions & Lifecycle
The actions the document supports (Create/Amend/Delete/Enquiry or others), their codes, and
any required follow-up verification flow. "Not specified" where absent.

## Core Business Workflows
Numbered WF-IDs. For each: the actor, the end-to-end flow, and the expected outcome.

## Business Rules & Validations
Numbered BR-IDs, atomic and testable. For each: the rule and its module; when it applies;
expected result when satisfied; expected result when violated (with the EXACT message/code if
